
Overview of noun hail

The noun hail has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (3) hail -- (precipitation of ice pellets when there are strong rising air currents)
2. hail -- (many objects thrown forcefully through the air; "a hail of pebbles"; "a hail of bullets")
3. hail -- (enthusiastic greeting)

Overview of verb hail

The verb hail has 5 senses (first 4 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (4) acclaim, hail, herald -- (praise vociferously; "The critics hailed the young pianist as a new Rubinstein")
2. (1) hail, come -- (be a native of; "She hails from Kalamazoo")
3. (1) hail -- (call for; "hail a cab")
4. (1) hail, herald -- (greet enthusiastically or joyfully)
5. hail -- (precipitate as small ice particles; "It hailed for an hour")
